Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.56,0:24:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't anything.\NVery interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.06,0:24:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Very interesting.\NThat's called illumination.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.42,0:25:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it went into me.\NThe light just kind of funneled into me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.92,0:25:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that is when we started teaching the work.\NSo it was almost like the guiding light, if you want to put it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.38,0:25:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But it did.\NIt changed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.94,0:25:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Several months after that, we live up in Sedona, as you all know.\NAnd I was driving down Upper Red Rock Loop Road.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.78,0:25:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden, this earth-changing phenomena took place\Nwhere you could see every single leaf on every tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.00,0:25:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Every rock seemed to be three-dimensional.\NAnd you're standing, as I'm driving down,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.60,0:25:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and I literally had to pull off the side of the road\Nand sit there for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.22,0:25:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you got the whole impression that the earth\Nand all your surroundings were a part of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.81,0:26:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're a part of it.\NIt was a very moving experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.94,0:26:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's hard to talk about it.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.58,0:26:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are the things we're going to be talking about.\NWhat is the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.67,0:26:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a place where you can become illuminated,\Nand become enlightened, for one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.09,0:26:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a world of great light.\NIt's a world of great spiritual opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.53,0:26:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's a place of maximum spiritual opportunity.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.53,0:26:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo I just thought we'd cover the basics,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.59,0:26:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll go on to the next slide.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.59,0:26:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to go through the review slides rather quickly.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.49,0:26:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to go through the review slides rather quickly.\NThese are the enlightened states.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.32,0:27:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the states of enlightenment.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.45,0:27:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the experiences which you can calibrate\Nall the way up to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.25,0:27:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the states of enlightenment,\Nand it goes all the way up to the archangels,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.12,0:27:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then all the way to divinity itself,\Nwhich is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.63,0:27:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I came out of the pits of hell,\Nin a state of eternal agony in the pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.94,0:27:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which I had fallen into through exploring the levels of consciousness,\Nand I began exploring the depths of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.62,0:27:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went into the levels of hell,\Nand first it was the higher hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.26,0:28:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,people just in agony and having their heads cut off\Nand stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.26,0:28:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I went into the depths of hell.\NAnd therefore, the depths of hell are beyond description.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.12,0:28:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I suggest to everybody that they avoid hell at all cost.\NEternal, hell is eternal agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.66,0:28:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the heavenly states are eternal bliss,\Nthe lower levels of hell were eternal agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.91,0:28:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember passing a sign that said,\NAbandon all hope, ye who enter here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.74,0:28:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Dante says.\NAnd how Dante knew it, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.74,0:28:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's what it says.\NAnd then you see suffering and agony
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.00,0:28:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hopelessness and despair that is forever.\NAnd as you go deeper into the pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.25,0:29:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize what forever means.\NThe horribleness of forever cut off from the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.89,0:29:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever agonizing despair.\NAnd that's why I advise people not to play with hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.40,0:29:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,People play with hell, they do.\NAnd it's like a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.91,0:29:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't want to go there.\NYou don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.71,0:29:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the pits of hell,\Nin the pits of hell where I was in eternity,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.03,0:29:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you can only experience eternity in the pits of hell.\NWhen you're in the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.67,0:29:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it went on for an eternity.\NAnd I was an atheist at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.22,0:29:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said,\NIf there is a God, I ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.38,0:29:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I went blank.\NAnd then when I came to,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.73,0:30:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the world had been transformed\Ninto the most incredible, radiant beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.08,0:30:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The light shone forth from the existence and divinity,\Nall that exists, the divinity of all that exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.75,0:30:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,shone forth in exquisite splendor.\NAnd that was the major transformation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.98,0:30:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of my own life.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.65,0:30:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why we got to talking about that.\NOh, yes, because of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.65,0:30:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this slide, yes.\NAll right, so what's the next slide, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.81,0:30:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo we said that most of the world's population
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.13,0:30:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,lives below the level of 200.\NActually, 85% of the world lives below
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.13,0:30:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what to us would be like the upper levels of hell,\Ndespair and poverty and crime and agony and hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.13,0:31:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's where 85% of the world's population lives.\NNow, they live below level 200, 85% of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.64,0:31:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, the average level of consciousness\Nof the world right now is, what did we say?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.41,0:31:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,204, yes.\NHow can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.46,0:31:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the few people, these are the few people\Nwho calibrate 250 and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.04,0:31:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how few they are compared to the mass\Nof people in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.23,0:31:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The great majority of people in the world\Nlive below level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.23,0:31:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can that be?\NWell, we'll turn, go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.26,0:31:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be because the 15% who calibrate over 200,\Ntheir relative power is so much greater
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.44,0:31:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,than the negativity.\NSo go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.98,0:32:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The 15% of the world calibrate, 15% calibrate above 200.\NCounterbalance is the 85% that calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.56,0:32:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that amazing?\NSo a group like this has a profound and significant impact
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.32,0:32:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,on the consciousness of the world.\NDoes that sound grandiose?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.98,0:32:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask the air.\NWhat I just said is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.55,0:32:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you sitting here in this audience right now,\Nhere present, are way over here and you're counterbalancing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.46,0:32:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a huge mass of the population.\NSo this audience here present now
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.74,0:32:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is counterbalancing literally millions.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.98,0:33:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This group here now is calibrating,\Nis counterbalancing the negativity literally of millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.98,0:33:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If that were not so,\Nthen humanity would just self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.02,0:33:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It would self-destruct.\NSo because of this 15%,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.02,0:33:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the 85% does not destroy itself.\NWe'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.08,0:33:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The evolution of consciousness over time,\Nthis is the scale of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.98,0:33:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, the animals starting way out\Nfrom the bacteria, protozoa,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.98,0:33:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,coming up through the fish, the octopus,\Nthe Komodo dragon, the dinosaur,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.98,0:33:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the whale, migratory birds.\NThen we get to the wild animals
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.49,0:33:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and the wolf, the hippopotamus.\NThen we get to the domestic pig.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.49,0:33:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good.\NWe finally get up to the piggies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.49,0:33:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, these are all killers.\NIn order to eat and live, they have to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.52,0:34:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we get to the peaceful animals\Nthat are herbivorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.52,0:34:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A deer doesn't have to kill anybody to survive.\NThe elk don't have to kill anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.55,0:34:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So the lower levels of consciousness\Nlive by the death of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.62,0:34:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So they are destructive to others,\Nso the only reason they stay alive
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.95,0:34:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is by killing you, a tiger or the lion.\NWe don't blame them for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.40,0:34:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't want to play with them.\NThen we move up the scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.20,0:34:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see, you come to the domestic animals,\Nyou come to the family dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.20,0:34:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gorilla, and Oscar the cat,\NAlex, the trained African gray parrot who talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.94,0:34:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Alex, you see, calibrates over 400.\NIn other words, Alex actually understands
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.94,0:35:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're saying.\NWhen you say to Alex, get me two blue cubes,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.16,0:35:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex understands two blue cubes.\NSo Alex is a very famous parrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.44,0:35:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And Coco, the trained gorilla, calibrates at 405.\NSo you are safer with Coco, the trained gorilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.95,0:35:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,than you are with 85% of the people on the planet.\NAll right, and here's where I go soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.72,0:35:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The kitty's purr is 500,\Nand a dog's wagging tail is 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.23,0:35:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've got three kitties home\Nand a doggie.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.33,0:35:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So this morning, all the kitties,\Nall three of them were around me purring away,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.33,0:35:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,giving me something to eat,\Nand the doggie's tail was wagging like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.39,0:36:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, now you have to stay home and guard the house.\NSo they have become man's companions,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.71,0:36:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,man's companions.\NOh, yes, we have, oh, I'm sorry about,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.43,0:36:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we have Broccoli, who is a talking parrot.\NAnd Broccoli carries on a conversation all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.46,0:36:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Never stops talking.\NAnd she calls to the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.58,0:36:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And she calls the kitties.\NHere, kitty, kitty, kitty, kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.13,0:36:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the dog's name?\NAnd she'll say, Kelsey, Kelsey.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.25,0:36:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dog runs over.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.30,0:36:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon as I was telling the dog, get away from the bird.\NSo then Kelsey will say, and then the bird will say,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.30,0:36:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,get away from that bird.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.30,0:36:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And what else did you, oh, she taught the bird to say,\Nshop till you drop, put it on the credit card.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.84,0:37:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Shop till you drop, put it on the credit card.\NThat is so funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.42,0:37:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll move along.\NOtherwise we'll never get through to the new material.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.42,0:37:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move to the next slide.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.64,0:37:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is the next slide.\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.64,0:37:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the level of the 400s.\NThis is the intellectual capital of civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.64,0:37:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the great books of the Western world,\Nwhich all calibrate in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.64,0:37:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the intellect of the 400s,\Nall the great scientists, Darwin, Copernicus,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.89,0:37:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great philosophers, Hegel, Hobbes,\NImmanuel Kant, Locke,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.38,0:38:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the structure of Western civilization.\NThis is what the Pope is worried is under threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.41,0:38:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He's afraid that the Western society is going to collapse.\NAnd he points to Europe and says that these level of the 400s
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.41,0:38:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are collapsing.\NAnd they are collapsing and calibrating lower and lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.60,0:38:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So Europe no longer calibrates as high as it once did.\NAnd the impact then of the great books of the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.95,0:38:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what has been substituted is social Marxism.\NSo what's being taught in a lot of colleges today
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.94,0:38:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the great books of the Western world,\Nwhich calibrated in the 400s, but cultural Marxism.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.94,0:38:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you see, Karl Marx calibrates at 130.\NSo if you're going to substitute 130
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.65,0:39:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for 455, Adam Smith,\Nthe wealth of nations is the basis of capitalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.65,0:39:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want to replace what calibrates at 455\Nwith collectivism, which calibrates at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.29,0:39:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And collectivism, where it has been tried,\Nhas caused collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.29,0:39:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In China, 10 million people starved to death.\N10 million starved to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.29,0:39:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Substituting this for this.\NSo the calibrated levels of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.48,0:39:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,are profoundly important.\NAnd the first thing I want to know about somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.58,0:39:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or a speaker, somebody on television,\Nis what does this person calibrate at?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.64,0:39:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Having calibrated thousands of things,\Nyou eventually get pretty good at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.67,0:39:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can guess, you know, almost within 10 degrees\Nof what level this person is speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.74,0:39:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you want to know is how much truth\Nis there to what they are saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.74,0:40:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next slide.\NWe'll skip this one. It's too difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.41,0:40:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll skip this one.\NWe'll skip this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.84,0:40:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is sort of an explanation\Nof why this muscle test works.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.84,0:40:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't understand it based on Newtonian physics,\Nwhich is based on cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.84,0:40:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a quantum effect.\NSo the understanding of the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.35,0:40:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that I demonstrate here with Susan all the time\Nhas to do with, the understanding is quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.54,0:40:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only, the best, nearest understanding to it\Nwould be reading the new book, Mindful Universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.58,0:40:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,by the professor of physics at Berkeley,\Nwhose name I always forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.09,0:40:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What was his name? Huh?\NHenry Stepp, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.47,0:41:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're really interested in understanding it,\Noh, here he is right here. I knew he was someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.30,0:41:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Stepp, yeah.\NSo the, what happens is you collapse the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.30,0:41:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,from potential to actual.\NSo what we're witnessing all the time is emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.43,0:41:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not witnessing causality.\NNothing is causing anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.53,0:41:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thinks in Newtonian terms of cause.\NWhat's happening is the potentiality becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.94,0:41:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,by an ascent of consciousness.\NWho did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.24,0:41:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?\NYou folks did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.00,0:42:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality becomes an actuality\Nby an ascent of the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.42,0:42:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are not caused.\NPotentiality emerges.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.42,0:42:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is this situation here has a potentiality.\NUnder the influence of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.58,0:42:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that potentiality becomes an actuality.\NUnder the influence of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.55,0:42:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what could be does become what it could be\Nif local conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.80,0:42:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you put water on it, it'll grow.\NIf you don't put water on it, it won't grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.80,0:42:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind thinks in Newtonian terms of cause and effect.\NActually, it's a quantum reality
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.27,0:42:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in which potentiality actualizes\Ndue to an ascent of the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.27,0:43:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The potentiality becomes an actuality.\NYou see, but that did it by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.98,0:43:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego jumps in.\NThe ego jumps in and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.98,0:43:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to put my arm out there.\NThat's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.59,0:43:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Help!\NIt decided to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.07,0:43:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the it that decided it?\NThere wasn't time to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.86,0:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Run through your mind.\NI think I'll put my arm out to demonstrate a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.86,0:43:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't time to think it.\NNo thinking went on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.02,0:43:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.\NNo thinking went on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.49,0:44:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No thinking went on.\NYou folks probably think
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.75,0:44:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything you do is because you think that.\NFess up, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.83,0:44:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There is that aspect of consciousness\Nwhich experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.88,0:44:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it presumes, it presumes that it is you.\NIt presumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.88,0:44:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you're not the experiencer.\NYou're the witness of these phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.35,0:44:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The phenomena are spontaneous.\NThe phenomena of life are happening of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.99,0:44:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Potentiality becoming an actuality.\NBecause, frankly, of the radiance of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.50,0:44:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the radiance of divinity,\Nall potentiality can become an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.76,0:45:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when the local conditions are right.\NNot because of your consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.05,0:45:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but because of the presence of divinity.\NThe consciousness of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.08,0:45:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is what allows all potentiality to become an actuality.\NThe source of all that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.37,0:45:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat makes it simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.85,0:45:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes it simple, doesn't it?\NThese are spiritual practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.42,0:45:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated all of them.\NAnd they're in one of the books, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.64,0:45:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you the calibrated level of consciousness\Nof various spiritual techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.02,0:45:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Practicing the golden rule.\NTurning fair wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.02,0:45:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See, they all calibrate around 540.\NGoing to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.02,0:45:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to communion.\NAll these things calibrate around 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.12,0:46:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Gregorian chants.\NOm Namah Shivaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.12,0:46:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Genuflection.\NKneeling to pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.31,0:46:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Clasping your hands.\NAll devotional acts are 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.24,0:46:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you experience a culture\Nwhere everyone greets the other person thusly,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.24,0:46:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in a different world.\NYou're in a different world
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.30,0:46:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,than Broadway in New York City.\NA world in which everyone greets everyone else this way
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.82,0:46:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledges divinity.\NI acknowledge divinity within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.10,0:46:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.78,0:46:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is too complicated.\NWe'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.19,0:46:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This has to do with brain function.\NNow, below level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.32,0:47:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,above and below 200,\Nyou have different brain function.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.90,0:47:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain function above 200\Nis different than the brain function below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.09,0:47:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say,\Nwhy don't people do this, that, and the other thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.15,0:47:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because they're operating\Nfrom a different side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.66,0:47:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal side of the brain\Nis interested in conquering,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.66,0:47:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and acquisition,\Nand things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.66,0:47:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the spiritual side of the brain\Nworks in a whole different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.66,0:47:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200,\Nyou have right brain dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.66,0:47:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens\Nas you become involved in spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.56,0:47:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or any spiritual practice\Nor any spiritual congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.82,0:47:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or attending a lecture like this\Nis that you,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.94,0:47:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you summon forth\Nwhat's classically been called
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.94,0:47:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the kundalini energy,\Na spiritual energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.97,0:48:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which classically is described\Nas going about the spine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.51,0:48:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini energy then rises\Nto the various chakras,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.54,0:48:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to the various chakras\Nor energy centers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.54,0:48:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And they get higher and higher\Nuntil finally they reach
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.70,0:48:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the crown chakra.\NBut we can tell,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.89,0:48:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so by being as loving as you can\Ntowards all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.89,0:48:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions,\Nyou're summoning forth
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.89,0:48:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field\Nto radiate up to the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.89,0:48:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you get up to the brow.\NYou begin to develop spiritual vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.05,0:48:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally to the crown chakra\Nand enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.05,0:48:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's actually\Na physiologic change in the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.34,0:48:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that occurs as a result\Nof becoming spiritually oriented,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.34,0:48:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually committed,\Njoining spiritual groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.34,0:49:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Practicing spiritual principles.\NJust simply praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.91,0:49:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Genuflecting.\NAll things that are symbolic
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.46,0:49:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of acknowledgement\Nof the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.46,0:49:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,as divinity.\NBegin to transform you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.81,0:49:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin to experience\Nand see the world differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.81,0:49:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we say,\Nwhat is the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.87,0:49:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it look like?\NWhat do you think the world is?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.87,0:49:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think the world is?\NIt pretty much depends considerably
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.87,0:49:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,on where your Kundalini energy\Nis risen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.87,0:49:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A person is risen to the third eye,\Nsees the world differently
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.94,0:49:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,than a person who is holding\Ntheir energy in the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.94,0:49:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding it in the spleen,\Nyou see an enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.77,0:49:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a world of attack and revenge,\Nattack and revenge,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.77,0:49:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,attack and revenge.\NThere are whole cultures
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.79,0:49:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,on the planet today\Nthat have a dominant effect
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.79,0:50:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on human history right now.\NThe whole culture lives in the spleen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.30,0:50:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole culture,\Nall the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.30,0:50:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the population,\Nthe country,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.30,0:50:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,lives in the spleen chakra.\NNot in the heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.39,0:50:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the spleen.\NRevenge,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.42,0:50:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,get even,\Ndominate,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.42,0:50:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,kill,\Nbehead,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.42,0:50:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,chop their heads off, etc.\NTo people who live in the heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.99,0:50:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this seems mysterious and unreal.\NAnd unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.25,0:50:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,they often go into denial\Nand say,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.25,0:50:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, people can't really be that way.\NOh, guess they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.82,0:50:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoops.\NLittle mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.82,0:50:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll move on.\NThe level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.27,0:50:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and social problems,\NI show this because
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.38,0:50:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this phenomenon is politicized.\NIn politicizing things,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.82,0:51:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a condition is blamed\Non other people
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.82,0:51:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or our circumstances,\Nyou see.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.82,0:51:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But now,\Nwhen we look at level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.27,0:51:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rate of unemployment,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.27,0:51:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of unemployment\Nis not related to available jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.50,0:51:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's related to level of consciousness.\NAt this consciousness level here,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.17,0:51:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,75% of the people are unemployed.\NIt has nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.16,0:51:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with how many jobs there are available.\NNothing to do with that whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.42,0:51:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of unemployment,\Nthe rate of crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.64,0:51:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of death,\Nthe rate of poverty,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.64,0:51:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the rate of violence,\Nthe rate of criminality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.63,0:51:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We can blame them\Non external factors,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.63,0:51:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see that they are all\Ncompletely related
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.63,0:51:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to the level of consciousness.\NWhat to this person
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.86,0:51:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is something we can do,\Nlet's go out and beat up people,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.86,0:51:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,would not even be thinkable\Nto these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.14,0:52:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So social problems\Nreflect completely and 100%
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.18,0:52:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness,\Nlevel of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.34,0:52:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next thing.\NThe rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.05,0:52:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here on the right-hand side,\Nwe see the rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.05,0:52:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At the lower levels,\N30% are happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.14,0:52:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we see,\Nno, I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.69,0:52:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,percent is 4%,\N3%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.91,0:52:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all below 10%.\NPeople who live in fear, 10%.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.91,0:52:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Angry, 12%.\NPride, a lot of people live in pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.91,0:52:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,22%.\NAll right, so you see
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.10,0:52:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at the higher the level\Nof consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.10,0:52:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the percent of people\Nwho are happy
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.10,0:52:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,goes up immensely.\NSo spiritually oriented,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.10,0:52:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say,\Nspiritually oriented people,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.10,0:53:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and over,\Nthe chances are probably 90%
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.10,0:53:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're relatively happy.\NYou're so used to being happy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.00,0:53:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you're not happy\Nfor a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.00,0:53:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you're unhappy.\NIf for a few minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.51,0:53:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you live where the rest\Nof the world lives all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.51,0:53:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you think it's a bad day.\NThey just think it's a normal day.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.51,0:53:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You get up depressed,\Nyou hate everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.51,0:53:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're overcome\Nwith greed and obsession
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.51,0:53:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with retaliation\Nand getting even with people,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.51,0:53:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and you think that's normal.\NThat's where they live all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.86,0:53:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get a negative thought\Nlike that,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.86,0:53:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you ask God to remove it.\NDear God, please help me
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.86,0:53:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to get over this angry thought,\Nand replace it by a pleasant thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.93,0:53:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next one.\NOh, we don't need to go into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.23,0:53:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go and move on to the next one.\NDid I have that one marked?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.97,0:53:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't really.\NWe calibrated the levels
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.97,0:54:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of many of the world's\Nmost famous spiritual teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.97,0:54:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a hundred or so.\NPeople are always writing me
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.38,0:54:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from someplace in the world,\Nand I tell them,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.06,0:54:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,look, we calibrated\Na hundred bona fide teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.06,0:54:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you can't find\Nyour guru on that hundred,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.06,0:54:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you're on your own.\NEven though there's
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.09,0:54:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a hundred well-respected\Nand verified teachers,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.09,0:54:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they always find, you know,\NRama Bumchipupu,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.09,0:54:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who says I should give him\Nall my money
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.60,0:54:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to bed with him.\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.56,0:54:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, next.\NNext, that's one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.58,0:54:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we'll move on.\NYeah, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.25,0:54:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway.\NAre you just doing
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.50,0:55:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the ones I circled?\NYes, we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.56,0:55:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I do?\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.33,0:55:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there many more circled?\NA few.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.83,0:55:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll go through\Nthe next ones real quick,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.83,0:55:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we won't stop\Nand play with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.83,0:55:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go,\Njust move real fast
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.12,0:55:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next one.\NSee the great places,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.12,0:55:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual places in the world.\NNext one, Golden Rule
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.82,0:55:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates for 405.\NGregorian Chants, 595.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.82,0:55:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NObligations of spiritual teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.82,0:55:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Declaration of responsibility,\Nintegrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.46,0:55:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can calibrate them all.\NWe'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.46,0:55:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,\Nhere's the crux
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.46,0:55:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of today's lecture.\NVeneration,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.46,0:55:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,perception,\Nand essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.46,0:55:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception and essence.\NThis is what the world sees
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.46,0:55:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and what it thinks\Nis going on,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.37,0:55:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is what\Nwe're going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.62,0:55:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about\Nin the next lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.82,0:55:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.82,0:55:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.82,0:56:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.82,0:56:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.82,0:56:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.10,0:56:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.10,0:56:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.10,0:56:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.10,0:56:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.33,0:56:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.33,0:56:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.62,0:56:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.78,0:56:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.78,0:56:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.78,0:56:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.78,0:56:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.78,0:56:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.78,0:56:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.97,0:56:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\Ncertain truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.13,0:56:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this, tell the sheep\Nand wolf in the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.74,0:56:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NYes, okay. Are we done yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.30,0:56:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't. We'll move on.\NI can't believe I circled
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.47,0:56:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all those. Move on to the\Nnext one. Move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.76,0:57:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly.\NAre we at the end?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.92,0:57:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.97,0:57:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Reminds me of the Wizard\Nof Oz. Do not look
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.43,0:57:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,behind this screen.\NI've got to keep an eye on the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.72,0:57:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have about\N15 minutes or so to break.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.38,0:57:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, alright. Freedom, morality\Nand ethics. That's not today's
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.42,0:57:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture. Here's what we're\Nsupposed to do today.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.35,0:57:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the slides on\Nwhat is the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.42,0:58:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we're\Ngoing to be talking about what is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.04,0:58:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the world? What is the purpose\Nof the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.29,0:58:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We discovered it's\NGod's karmic bailout
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.42,0:58:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,plan. I don't know. I can't\Nget the slides right today.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.97,0:58:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We need\Nthe world. We're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.07,0:59:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the world today.\NHey!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.92,0:59:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,157. So we're missing\Nthe first three.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.92,0:59:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the world? Oh boy.\NWow, we're ahead of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.53,0:59:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. So there's no\Npoint of cursing your existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.28,0:59:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh God, why was I\Nborn?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.19,0:59:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Being born a human is rare.\NFortunate. The consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.07,0:59:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of good karma. If we calibrate\Nthat, that comes out at
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.73,0:59:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,455. Now that's\Nwhat the Buddha teaches pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.20,0:59:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On\Nthe one hand, it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.70,1:00:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,good thing to be born a human because\Nthere are karmic improvements
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.52,1:00:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make on yourself.\NOn the other hand, the Buddha warns us
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.52,1:00:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoid being reborn as\Na human.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.92,1:00:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Old age\Nsuffering and death.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.68,1:00:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Navoid it if you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.82,1:00:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you are here, then\Nbe glad
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.56,1:00:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and fortunate\Nthat you are here because of good karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.10,1:00:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because\Nhere you can overcome
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.88,1:00:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,negative karma and gain positive\Nkarma. So to me
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.38,1:00:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is a world of maximum\Nspiritual opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.60,1:00:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you can gain good\Nkarma and undo negative
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.75,1:00:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. Being born\Na human is fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.23,1:00:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the consequence of good karma\Ncalibrates at 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.05,1:00:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we'll take a negative\Nview. The world is a trap of illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.10,1:00:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nsalvation depends on non-attachment
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.06,1:01:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to its linear and emotional\Nqualities. That only
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.76,1:01:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 230.\NThat only calibrates at 230.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.82,1:01:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The perceived world\Nis the result of the projection
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.53,1:01:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of human consciousness\Nand therefore akin to a Rorschach
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.71,1:01:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,card, 450.\NAs a psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.01,1:01:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that always appealed to me.\NYou see, you project
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.69,1:01:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,out onto the world what\Nyou think it is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.33,1:01:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because of who you are.\NNot because of what the world
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.83,1:01:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is. However, you can\Nmake gross miscalculations
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.93,1:01:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, here kitty, kitty,\Nkitty to the tiger.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.99,1:01:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Or play\Nwith the chimpanzee.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.06,1:01:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Or tame\Na white tiger.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.94,1:01:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so\Nmiscalculating with wild animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.34,1:01:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the wild animal\Ndoesn't respond
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.66,1:02:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as a person. So I'll explain\Nto you the wild animal phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.34,1:02:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens with white tigers,\Ntrained lions,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.68,1:02:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the lady and the lion. In the end\Nthe lion kills the lady, or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.39,1:02:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,These trained animals, they suddenly go\Nberserk and kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.10,1:02:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And why you cannot trust them.\NIt's because
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.42,1:02:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,animals have a group consciousness.\NAnimals have
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.54,1:02:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a perceived\Nmemory.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.95,1:02:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They have an individual\Nmemory. But their
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.22,1:02:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is a group consciousness.\NI first learned this
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.24,1:02:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was watching a flock of birds.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.16,1:02:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought the birds are\Nfollowing each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.06,1:02:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All thousands of birds are\Nfollowing each other. The sky is black with birds.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.94,1:02:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought,\Nhow can they stay in formation like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.20,1:03:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Each bird stays in formation\Nlike a bunch of flying tigers.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.44,1:03:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a bunch of\Nairplanes, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.88,1:03:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway,\Nand then I suddenly
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.81,1:03:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,got what's going on.\NEach bird in that flock
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.03,1:03:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is not following the other birds.\NBelieve that?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.60,1:03:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dumb.\NNo, each bird is not
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.00,1:03:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,following the other birds\Nat all. The assumption
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.18,1:03:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the bird is following the flock\Ndue to a density and how
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.18,1:03:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,close they are to the other birds, etc.\NWhat's happening is that there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.40,1:03:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is a pattern\Nin their mind, and each
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.14,1:03:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,bird is following not the other\Nbird at all, but
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.11,1:03:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy pattern in their minds.\NIsn't that amazing?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.30,1:03:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Each bird now is\Nlike a radio turn to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.86,1:04:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the same radio frequency.\NSo each bird
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.15,1:04:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is following an inner pattern.\NThat's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.72,1:04:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Each bird\Nis following an inner imprint,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.72,1:04:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,an inner pattern.\NEach bird is therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.67,1:04:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,individual and yet\Nfollows a group consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.88,1:04:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So all animals\Nfollow a group consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.28,1:04:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nan ape that seems tame,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.54,1:04:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,now, his memory\Ntrack is that this is a safe
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.58,1:04:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,place to be,\Nbut his group consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.75,1:04:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is that of the animal.\NAnd at any moment, the white tiger
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.09,1:04:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,will tear your\Ncarotid artery right out
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.61,1:04:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's responding\Nto the group consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.34,1:04:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, any wild animal\Ncannot be trusted
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.58,1:05:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at the level of absolute trust.\NIt's only a matter of time
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.42,1:05:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,before his\Ngroup consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.78,1:05:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,will take over.\NAnd the lion eats the lady.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.34,1:05:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The white tiger rips out the neck\Nof the man.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.29,1:05:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The chimp tears at the lady's face.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.92,1:05:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal is only\Nvery partially
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.22,1:05:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,who you think it is.\NIt is more 95%
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.44,1:05:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the instinctual animal.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.56,1:05:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you can never safely turn your back\Non a wild animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.94,1:05:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you get away\Nwith it many times
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.28,1:05:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean it's safe to do.\NBut I just thought I'd tell you,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.46,1:05:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they respond to a group consciousness.\NBelow level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.02,1:05:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,people respond to a group consciousness.\NBelow 200, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.21,1:05:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So the people living\Nin a violent community,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.83,1:06:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only a matter of time\Nbefore they become violent.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.70,1:06:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a matter of time\Nbefore they begin doing dog
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.28,1:06:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,fighting and various things like that.\NThe group consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.96,1:06:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to dominate then.\NSo all of us are
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.24,1:06:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,under the influence of a group\Ncultural consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.56,1:06:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,plus an individual consciousness.\NAnd as you become
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.19,1:06:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually evolved,\Nyour consciousness becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.07,1:06:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively more immune\Nto negativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.62,1:06:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And people say, let's go in town\Nand shoot them all up.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.38,1:06:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, I don't feel like it today.\NIt just doesn't appeal to you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.79,1:06:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a matter of being a goody-goody.\NIt's just that it has no longer
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.27,1:06:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,any kind of reality to you.\NIt has no kind of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.36,1:06:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The perceived world is a result\Nof a projection of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.14,1:07:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore like a Rorschach card.\NSo you project out onto the world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.67,1:07:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your view of the world.\NAnd depending on what your level of consciousness is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.98,1:07:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you can project out onto the world your view of the world.\NAnd depending on what your level of consciousness is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.26,1:07:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I always give the example\Nof going to New York City.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.26,1:07:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I love New York City.\NPeople will come back from New York City
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.98,1:07:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, you know, they're all cold\Nand unfriendly there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.36,1:07:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Another person will come back\Nand say, everybody was friendly there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.13,1:07:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I notice when I go to New York City,\Nyou can stop anybody on the street
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.27,1:07:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and start a conversation\Njust like you knew them forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.95,1:07:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, what do you think of that?\NThey're going up there and the guy will say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.05,1:07:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,hell, I think they're spending a lot of taxpayer money on that.\NYou're right in the middle of a conversation
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.39,1:07:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,like you knew you for 20 years.\NPeople are very, very friendly.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.64,1:07:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because you're friendly and benign.\NBut if you're below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.75,1:07:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they say, listen, I don't know you\Nand they'll walk away.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.35,1:07:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you see then\Nis not what you think is out there
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.89,1:08:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but a projection of your own self.\NAll right, so we're going to stop here
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.66,1:08:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and take a break for how long?\N15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.96,1:08:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to review\Nfor those that are new,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.85,1:08:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because quite a few knew,\Nall that we've summarized
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.27,1:08:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so far,\Nand that'll bring us up to date
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.36,1:08:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for today's lecture.
